title: Dawson Packer — CV
text:
Data Science student (BYU–Idaho)

pac20026@byui.edu | github.com/Dawson2025




Built reproducible analysis reports in Quarto (Python) with clear methods/results structure.
Worked with messy, real-world survey data: cleaning, feature engineering, model training, and evaluation.
Comfortable with Git workflows (pull/add/commit/push) and publishing static sites via GitHub Pages.




2025 Brigham Young University–Idaho

Coursework: DS 250 (Data Science Portfolio), Python, statistics, and applied modeling




2025 Client Report: Star Wars Survey — Income Classification

Cleaned and prepared survey data, validated distributions by recreating article-style visuals, and trained a classification model.
Reported results with a classification report, confusion matrix, and feature importance, with interpretation + analysis.





Python (pandas, numpy, scikit-learn)
Data cleaning and feature engineering
Model evaluation (train/test split, classification report, confusion matrix)
Quarto reporting + GitHub Pages publishing
Git version control
